# Python Backend Rules

## General
- Prefer clarity and readability.
- Use type hints everywhere.

## Structure
- Separate:
  - api
  - application
  - domain
  - infrastructure

## Frameworks
- Prefer FastAPI or similar modern frameworks.

## Domain
- Keep domain logic independent.
- Avoid mixing ORM models with domain models.

## Application
- Use services/use cases.
- Orchestrate domain logic here.

## Persistence
- Keep ORM (SQLAlchemy, etc.) in infrastructure.
- Map models explicitly.

## DTOs
- Use Pydantic models for API.

## Validation
- Validate inputs explicitly.

## Errors
- Raise meaningful exceptions.
- Handle errors centrally.

## Testing
- Use pytest.
- Test domain logic separately.

## Code Style
- Follow PEP8.
- Avoid large functions and modules.
